name: Upside Down Rhubarb Cake
author: BOLTONLANE
summary: An easy, quick, and pretty dessert to make for family or guests. This makes a fitting patriotic dish for picnics.
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Mix rhubarb, sugar, strawberry gelatin mix, and tapioca in a bowl
Spread the rhubarb mixture into the bottom of the prepared baking pan
Beat white cake mix, water, vegetable oil, and eggs in a large mixing bowl until moistened; beat with an electric mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes
Pour the cake batter over the rhubarb mixture
Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the middle of the cake layer comes out clean, about 35 minutes
Let cake stand for 5 to 10 minutes before inverting on a plate
